{
  "question_text": "<h3>Asteroid Collision</h3><p>Simulate collisions of asteroids moving left and right with given sizes.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "asteroids.",
  "output_format": "Array.",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 10^4"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use a stack to track moving asteroids. For each asteroid, if it moves right, push it. If it moves left, while it can collide with the top of stack (which must be moving right), resolve the collision. If both are same size, pop both. If moving left is bigger, pop stack. If stack is empty or top is moving left, push moving left.",
  "answer": "def asteroidCollision(asteroids):\n    stack = []\n    for a in asteroids:\n        while stack and a < 0 < stack[-1]:\n            if stack[-1] < -a:\n                stack.pop()\n                continue\n            elif stack[-1] == -a:\n                stack.pop()\n            break\n        else:\n            stack.append(a)\n    return stack",
